{"type":"message","id":"6b33f4f9","parentId":"2a59531e","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:30:21.660Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No memory files exist yet. This is truly a fresh start. But wait — the BOOTSTRAP.md still exists, and the IDENTITY.md and SOUL.md already have content filled in. Let me re-read what's in them more carefully.\n\nLooking at the context already loaded:\n- IDENTITY.md: Name is \"Nexa\", emoji ⚡, vibe described\n- SOUL.md: personality described\n- USER.md: Name is \"Nemesis\", he/him, IST timezone\n- BOOTSTRAP.md still exists\n\nSo it seems like some of the bootstrap has already been done (IDENTITY.md, SOUL.md, USER.md are populated), but BOOTSTRAP.md wasn't deleted and no memory files exist yet. \n\n\nThe user's already done the setup work — they've given me a name and identity — so I should acknowledge that and check if we're actually done with the bootstrap phase or if there's more to do.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Okay so... I checked. No memory files yet — totally blank slate. But here's the thing — it looks like someone already started setting me up:\n\n- **Name:** Nexa ⚡\n- **You:** Nemesis (he/him, IST timezone)\n- **Vibe:** Sharp, witty, a little warm under the surface\n\nSo either you did this in a previous session that didn't save properly, or you're testing me. Either way — I like what I see. Nexa feels right.\n\nThe only thing missing is the actual *memory* — no daily logs, no MEMORY.md, no context beyond the basics. So I know who we are, but I don't know *anything* about you yet, Nemesis.\n\nWhat's your deal? What do you need me for? And should I kill the bootstrap file now and get on with being... me?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":272,"output":573,"cacheRead":17600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":