ompt*\" [ref=e118]: portrait | wide angle shot of eyes off to one side of frame, lucid dream-like woman, looking off in distance ::8 style | daydreampunk with glowing skin and eyes, styled in headdress, beautiful, she is dripping in neon lights, very colorful blue, green, purple, bioluminescent, glowing ::8 background | forest, vivid neon wonderland, particles, blue, green, purple ::7 parameters | rule of thirds, golden ratio, assymetric composition, hyper- maximalist, octane render, photorealism, cinematic realism, unreal engine, 8k ::7 --ar 16:9 --s 1000\n                  - generic [ref=e120]:\n                    - generic [ref=e121]:\n                      - generic [ref=e122]: Additional Settings\n                      - button \"More\" [ref=e124] [cursor=pointer]:\n                        - generic [ref=e125]: More\n                        - img [ref=e126]\n                    - paragraph [ref=e128]: Customize your input with more control.\n                - generic [ref=e131]:\n                  - button \"Reset\" [ref=e132] [cursor=pointer]\n                  - link \"Sign in to run\" [ref=e134] [cursor=pointer]:\n                    - /url: /login?returnTo=%2Fmodels%2Ffal-ai%2Fflux%2Fschnell%2Fplayground%3FrestoreInputKey%3Dfal-ai%2Fflux%2Fschnell\n            - generic [ref=e135]:\n              - generic [ref=e136]:\n                - generic [ref=e138]:\n                  - generic [ref=e139]:\n                    - heading \"Result\" [level=3] [ref=e140]\n                    - generic [ref=e141]: Idle\n                  - group [ref=e143]:\n                    - radio \"Preview\" [checked] [ref=e144] [cursor=pointer]:\n                      - img [ref=e145]\n                      - generic [ref=e149]: Preview\n                    - radio \"JSON\" [ref=e150] [cursor=pointer]:\n                      - img [ref=e151]\n                      - generic [ref=e156]: JSON\n                - generic [ref=e160]:\n                  - generic [ref=e163]:\n                    - img \"m0K3P3JUR_Brcf7mxk3tl.png\" [ref=e165] [cursor=pointer]\n                    - link [ref=e167] [cursor=pointer]:\n                      - /url: https://fal.media/files/tiger/m0K3P3JUR_Brcf7mxk3tl.png\n                      - img [ref=e168]\n                  - generic [ref=e170]:\n                    - heading \"What would you like to do next?\" [level=4] [ref=e171]\n                    - link \"Download\" [ref=e173] [cursor=pointer]:\n                      - /url: https://fal.media/files/tiger/m0K3P3JUR_Brcf7mxk3tl.png\n                      - img [ref=e174]\n                      - text: Download\n                - generic [ref=e177]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e179]:\n                    - text: Your request took\n                    - generic [ref=e180]: 0.37 seconds\n                    - text: and will cost\n                    - generic [ref=e181]: $0.003\n                    - text: per megapixel.\n                  - paragraph [ref=e182]: Images are billed by rounding up to the nearest megapixel.\n              - generic [ref=e184] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - heading \"Logs\" [level=3] [ref=e185]\n                - button \"Show\" [ref=e187]:\n                  - text: Show\n                  - img [ref=e188]\n          - generic [ref=e194]:\n            - heading \"Readme\" [level=3] [ref=e195]\n            - heading \"FLUX.1 [schnell] - Ultra-Fast Text-to-Image Generation\" [level=4] [ref=e196]\n            - paragraph [ref=e197]: Transform your ideas into stunning visuals in seconds with FLUX.1 [schnell], a powerful 12 billion parameter flow transformer designed for production-ready image generation. Whether you're creating content for commercial projects or personal artwork, FLUX.1 [schnell] delivers exceptional quality in just 1-4 inference steps with sub-second results.\n            - heading \"Key Capabilities\" [level=5] [ref=e198]\n            - paragraph [ref=e199]: \"Create high-fidelity images with remarkable speed and precision. FLUX.1 [schnell] excels at:\"\n            - list [ref=e200]:\n              - listitem [ref=e201]: Professional-grade image generation with precise detail control\n              - listitem [ref=e202]: Lightning-fast inference (1-4 steps with sub-second results)\n              - listitem [ref=e203]: Commercial-ready outputs with full usage rights\n              - listitem [ref=e204]: Consistent style maintenance across multiple generations\n              - listitem [ref=e205]: Advanced prompt interpretation for accurate results\n              - listitem [ref=e206]: Text-to-image and image-to-image generation capabilities\n            - heading \"Popular Use Cases\" [level=5] [ref=e207]\n            - paragraph [ref=e208]:\n              - strong [ref=e209]: Content Creation\n              - text: Generate marketing visuals, social media assets, and blog illustrations at scale. Perfect for agencies and content teams who need consistent, high-quality imagery.\n            - paragraph [ref=e210]:\n              - strong [ref=e211]: Product Development\n              - text: Create concept art, UI mockups, and design variations for rapid prototyping. Ideal for designers exploring visual directions.\n            - paragraph [ref=e212]:\n              - strong [ref=e213]: E-commerce\n              - text: Generate product lifestyle images, seasonal campaigns, and A/B testing visuals to boost conversion rates.\n            - paragraph [ref=e214]:\n              - strong [ref=e215]: Entertainment\n              - text: Produce game assets, storyboard illustrations, and creative concept art for media projects.\n            - heading \"Getting Started\" [level=5] [ref=e216]\n            - paragraph [ref=e217]: \"Getting up and running with FLUX.1 [schnell] is straightforward. Here's how to begin:\"\n            - list [ref=e218]:\n              - listitem [ref=e219]: \"Install your preferred SDK:\"\n            - paragraph [ref=e220]: \"For JavaScript/TypeScript:\"\n            - generic [ref=e222]:\n              - generic [ref=e223]:\n                - code [ref=e225]: bash\n                - button \"Copy\" [ref=e226] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e227]:\n                    - img [ref=e229]\n                    - img [ref=e232]\n              - code [ref=e236]:\n                - generic [ref=e237]: npm install --save @fal-ai/client\n            - paragraph [ref=e238]: \"For Python:\"\n            - generic [ref=e240]:\n              - generic [ref=e241]:\n                - code [ref=e243]: bash\n                - button \"Copy\" [ref=e244] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e245]:\n                    - img [ref=e247]\n                    - img [ref=e250]\n              - code [ref=e254]:\n                - generic [ref=e255]: pip install fal-client\n            - list [ref=e256]:\n              - listitem [ref=e257]: \"Configure your credentials:\"\n            - generic [ref=e259]:\n              - generic [ref=e260]:\n                - code [ref=e262]: typescript\n                - button \"Copy\" [ref=e263] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e264]:\n                    - img [ref=e266]\n                    - img [ref=e269]\n              - code [ref=e273]:\n                - generic [ref=e274]: \"import { fal } from '@fal-ai/client'\"\n                - generic [ref=e275]: \"fal.config({\"\n                - generic [ref=e276]: \"credentials: 'YOUR_FAL_KEY'\"\n                - generic [ref=e277]: \"})\"\n            - list [ref=e278]:\n              - listitem [ref=e279]: \"Generate your first image:\"\n            - generic [ref=e281]:\n              - generic [ref=e282]:\n                - code [ref=e284]: typescript\n                - button \"Copy\" [ref=e285] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e286]:\n                    - img [ref=e288]\n                    - img [ref=e291]\n              - code [ref=e295]:\n                - generic [ref=e296]: \"const result = await fal.subscribe('fal-ai/flux/schnell', {\"\n                - generic [ref=e297]: \"input: {\"\n                - generic [ref=e298]: \"prompt: \\\"A serene mountain landscape at sunset, hyperrealistic style\\\",\"\n                - generic [ref=e299]: \"num_inference_steps: 4\"\n                - generic [ref=e300]: \"}\"\n                - generic [ref=e301]: \"})\"\n            - heading \"Technical Specifications\" [level=5] [ref=e302]\n            - paragraph [ref=e303]: \"FLUX.1 [schnell] represents the latest in flow-based architecture:\"\n            - heading \"Architecture\" [level=6] [ref=e304]\n            - list [ref=e305]:\n              - listitem [ref=e306]:\n                - strong [ref=e307]: 12B parameter flow transformer\n                - text: optimized for speed\n              - listitem [ref=e308]:\n                - strong [ref=e309]: Flow-based distillation\n                - text: for ultra-fast inference\n              - listitem [ref=e310]:\n                - strong [ref=e311]: 1-4 inference steps\n                - text: \"(default: 4 steps)\"\n              - listitem [ref=e312]:\n                - strong [ref=e313]: Sub-second response times\n                - text: for fastest generation\n              - listitem [ref=e314]:\n                - strong [ref=e315]: Commercial usage rights\n                - text: included\n            - heading \"API Parameters\" [level=6] [ref=e316]\n            - list [ref=e317]:\n              - listitem [ref=e318]:\n                - strong [ref=e319]: prompt\n                - text: \": Text description of desired image\"\n              - listitem [ref=e320]:\n                - strong [ref=e321]: image_size\n                - text: \": Various preset sizes or custom dimensions\"\n              - listitem [ref=e322]:\n                - strong [ref=e323]: num_inference_steps\n                - text: \": Generation steps (default: 4)\"\n              - listitem [ref=e324]:\n                - strong [ref=e325]: num_images\n                - text: \": Number of images to generate (default: 1)\"\n              - listitem [ref=e326]:\n                - strong [ref=e327]: seed\n                - text: \": For reproducible results\"\n              - listitem [ref=e328]:\n                - strong [ref=e329]: enable_safety_checker\n                - text: \": Content safety filtering (default: true)\"\n              - listitem [ref=e330]:\n                - strong [ref=e331]: output_format\n                - text: \": Image format (default: PNG)\"\n            - heading \"Performance\" [level=6] [ref=e332]\n            - list [ref=e333]:\n              - listitem [ref=e334]:\n                - strong [ref=e335]: Sub-second response times\n                - text: for rapid generation\n              - listitem [ref=e336]:\n                - strong [ref=e337]: Fastest AI image generation\n                - text: among FLUX models\n              - listitem [ref=e338]:\n                - strong [ref=e339]: Concurrent request handling\n                - text: capability\n              - listitem [ref=e340]:\n                - strong [ref=e341]: Enterprise-grade reliability\n                - text: and uptime\n            - heading \"Best Practices\" [level=5] [ref=e342]\n            - paragraph [ref=e343]: \"To achieve optimal results with FLUX.1 [schnell]:\"\n            - list [ref=e344]:\n              - listitem [ref=e345]: Write detailed, specific prompts that describe both content and style\n              - listitem [ref=e346]: Use 4 steps (default) for balanced speed/quality, adjust as needed\n              - listitem [ref=e347]: Leverage the fastest generation for iterative workflows\n              - listitem [ref=e348]: Monitor API usage through the dashboard for optimization\n              - listitem [ref=e349]: Take advantage of sub-second generation for real-time applications\n            - heading \"Integration Guide\" [level=5] [ref=e350]\n            - paragraph [ref=e351]: \"FLUX.1 [schnell] integrates seamlessly into existing workflows:\"\n            - list [ref=e352]:\n              - listitem [ref=e353]: Set up authentication using environment variables\n              - listitem [ref=e354]: Initialize the client in your application\n              - listitem [ref=e355]: Implement error handling and retries\n              - listitem [ref=e356]: Add response validation\n              - listitem [ref=e357]: Configure webhook endpoints for async processing\n            - heading \"Advanced Features\" [level=5] [ref=e358]\n            - paragraph [ref=e359]: \"Take advantage of FLUX.1 [schnell]'s advanced capabilities:\"\n            - heading \"Speed Optimization\" [level=6] [ref=e360]\n            - paragraph [ref=e361]: FLUX.1 [schnell] is specifically optimized for ultra-fast generation, making it ideal for applications requiring rapid iteration and real-time image creation.\n            - heading \"Image Size Control\" [level=6] [ref=e362]\n            - paragraph [ref=e363]: Generate images at various dimensions with preset sizes or custom width/height configurations to match your specific requirements.\n            - heading \"Batch Processing\" [level=6] [ref=e364]\n            - paragraph [ref=e365]: Create multiple variations efficiently with built-in batching support for rapid prototyping and content generation.\n            - heading \"Turbo Mode\" [level=6] [ref=e366]\n            - paragraph [ref=e367]: The \"schnell\" (German for \"fast\") variant is the turbo mode of the FLUX.1 family, prioritizing speed while maintaining high image quality.\n            - heading \"Pricing and Usage\" [level=5] [ref=e368]\n            - paragraph [ref=e369]: \"Your request will cost $0.003 per megapixel. Images are billed by rounding up to the nearest megapixel. Our transparent, usage-based pricing scales with your needs:\"\n            - list [ref=e370]:\n              - listitem [ref=e371]:\n                - strong [ref=e372]: Most cost-effective\n                - text: \": $0.003 per megapixel\"\n              - listitem [ref=e373]:\n                - strong [ref=e374]: Commercial usage rights\n                - text: included\n              - listitem [ref=e375]:\n                - strong [ref=e376]: No subscription fees\n                - text: or minimum commitments\n              - listitem [ref=e377]:\n                - strong [ref=e378]: Fastest generation\n                - text: with competitive pricing\n            - paragraph [ref=e379]:\n              - link \"View detailed pricing\" [ref=e380] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: https://fal.ai/pricing\n              - text: or\n              - link \"contact sales\" [ref=e381] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: mailto:support@fal.ai\n              - text: for enterprise solutions.\n            - heading \"Support and Resources\" [level=5] [ref=e382]\n            - paragraph [ref=e383]: \"We're here to help you succeed with FLUX.1 [schnell]:\"\n            - list [ref=e384]:\n              - listitem [ref=e385]:\n                - strong [ref=e386]: Documentation\n                - text: \": Comprehensive API references and guides\"\n              - listitem [ref=e387]:\n                - strong [ref=e388]: Community\n                - text: \": Active Discord community for peer support\"\n              - listitem [ref=e389]:\n                - strong [ref=e390]: Technical Support\n                - text: \": Direct assistance through support tickets\"\n              - listitem [ref=e391]:\n                - strong [ref=e392]: Examples\n                - text: \": Growing library of implementation examples\"\n              - listitem [ref=e393]:\n                - strong [ref=e394]: Updates\n                - text: \": Regular model improvements and feature additions\"\n            - paragraph [ref=e395]: Get started today and experience the fastest AI image generation available. Create your API key now and begin transforming your ideas into stunning visuals with FLUX.1 [schnell].\n            - paragraph [ref=e396]:\n              - link \"Get Started Now\" [ref=e397] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: https://fal.ai/login\n              - text: \"|\"\n              - link \"View Documentation\" [ref=e398] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: https://docs.fal.ai/\n              - text: \"|\"\n              - link \"Try FLUX Schnell\" [ref=e399] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: https://fal.ai/models/fal-ai/flux/schnell\n    - contentinfo [ref=e401]:\n      - generic [ref=e402]:\n        - generic [ref=e403]:\n          - generic [ref=e404]:\n            - heading \"Learn More\" [level=4] [ref=e405]\n            - generic [ref=e406]:\n              - link \"Status\" [ref=e407] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: https://status.fal.ai\n              - link \"About Us\" [ref=e408] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: /about\n              - link \"Documentation\" [ref=e409] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: https://docs.fal.ai\n              - link \"Careers\" [ref=e410] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/fal\n              - link \"Pricing\" [ref=e411] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: /pricing\n              - link \"Blog\" [ref=e412] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: https://blog.fal.ai\n              - link \"Enterprise\" [ref=e413] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: /enterprise\n              - link \"Get in touch\" [ref=e414] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: mailto:support@fal.ai\n              - link \"Gen Media Report 2026\" [ref=e415] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: /gen-media-report-volume-1\n              - link \"Grants\" [ref=e416] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: /grants\n              - link \"Events\" [ref=e417] [cursor=pointer]:\n                - /url: /events\n     