{"type":"message","id":"3080e836","parentId":"7a717cbb","timestamp":"2026-03-27T16:53:50.532Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can only see my direct chat with Nemesis. The group chat session hasn't appeared yet. This might be because:\n1. The group chat messages come through a different session\n2. Or the message hasn't been received yet in the group\n\nThe user said \"check the message I sent\" - he might have sent a message in the group already. But I'm only seeing the direct chat session. \n\nIn Telegram groups, the bot needs to be able to see messages. The config mentioned that `groupPolicy` is set to \"allowlist\" but `groupAllowFrom` is empty, which means \"all group messages will be silently dropped.\"\n\nThis is likely the issue! The group messages are being dropped because the group allow policy isn't configured properly. Let me tell the user about this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I think I know what's happening. The system is set up to only allow direct messages from you — group chats are currently blocked by default. That means even though you added me to the group, I can't actually see or respond to messages there.\n\nYou'd need to either:\n1. **Add the group chat ID to the allow list** — so I can receive messages from it\n2. **Or set group policy to \"open\"** — so I can join any group\n\nWant me to fix this config, or do you know the Telegram group chat ID so I can add it specifically?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":875,"output":451,"cacheRead":79296,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80622,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774630400502}}
