{"type":"message","id":"1f8368fd","parentId":"8db6a2d5","timestamp":"2026-03-27T16:56:44.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know how to get the Telegram group chat ID. There are a few ways:\n\n1. Forward a message from the group to a bot like @userinfobot or @getidsbot\n2. Use the Telegram API\n3. I could check the OpenClaw logs to see if the group message was received (even if dropped by policy)\n\nLet me suggest the easiest method.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Easiest way — in Telegram:\n\n1. Open your group chat\n2. Forward any message from the group to **@userinfobot** or **@getidsbot**\n3. It'll reply with the group chat ID (usually starts with `-100`)\n\nOr if you want me to check — I can look at the OpenClaw logs to see if the group message was received even though it was dropped. That might already show me the chat ID.\n\nWant me to check the logs?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":1514,"output":269,"cacheRead":79104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80887,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774630593301}}
