{"type":"message","id":"1a2fd44a","parentId":"f0772ca9","timestamp":"2026-03-27T17:25:14.644Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Can't create a persistent session without a thread. Let me check if there's another approach. Actually, the group chat messages in Telegram come through the bot, and the bot routes them to a session based on the chat_id. I don't think I can route them to a different session from within this session.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The real solution is probably to configure the OpenClaw gateway to route group chats differently, but that's a config-level thing, not something I can do from within a session.\n\nLet me be honest with the user about the limitation and suggest alternatives.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Honestly, I can't create a separate always-on sub-agent for the group — sub-agents need a thread binding and I don't have that set up for Telegram groups.\n\nBut here's what actually works: **the group messages already come to me separately**. When someone messages in the group, it's a different session context. I won't get \"distracted\" — I can handle both your direct chat and the group independently.\n\nThe real fix is just making sure the group config is solid. Let me check if messages from the group are actually flowing in now:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_334625892f8846dcafce29ae","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -30 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-03-27.log 2>&1 | grep -i \"group\\|-10036\\|skip\\|drop\\|inbound\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":572,"output":429,"cacheRead":88960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89961,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774632299841}}
