{"type":"message","id":"3d1a2633","parentId":"a3862f90","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:39:17.608Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config shows `groupPolicy: \"open\"` and `groups: {}`. But the groups setting is an empty object. The group policy is set to \"open\" which should allow any group. But let me check if the gateway was restarted with this config.\n\nAlso, the earlier log had a warning: \"Invalid allowFrom entry: \"-1003606834639\" - allowFrom/groupAllowFrom authorization expects numeric Telegram sender user IDs only. To allow a Telegram group or supergroup, add its negative chat ID under \"channels.telegram.groups\" instead.\"\n\nAnd now groups is an empty object `{}`. The groupPolicy is \"open\" though, so it should accept all groups.\n\n\nThe gateway might be running an older config, or the group messages haven't come through yet—Sravya could just be quiet. Let me test by sending a message to the group myself to see if it actually works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Config looks good — `groupPolicy: \"open\"` means any group should work. Let me test by sending to the group and checking if messages come back."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a3c2717be0cb413a8d047fd4","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"telegram","message":"Hey! 👋 Can someone send a message here so I can confirm I'm receiving group messages?","target":"-1003606834639"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":2102,"output":491,"cacheRead":95936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98529,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774676344370}}
