{"type":"message","id":"4088aafe","parentId":"9595ebcb","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:39:56.524Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK I sent a message to the group. But the question is whether I can RECEIVE messages from the group. The user wants to know if I can differentiate between two people (Nemesis and Sravya) in the group.\n\nThe issue might be that even with `groupPolicy: \"open\"`, the bot still needs to be able to receive messages. In Telegram, a bot can see messages in a group if:\n1. It's added to the group\n2. It has the right privacy settings (by default, bots only see commands and messages that mention them)\n\nThe user needs to either:\n- Add the bot to the group and disable privacy mode\n- Or mention the bot in messages\n\nActually, in Telegram, when a bot is added to a group, it can only see messages if:\n\n\n- The bot's privacy mode is disabled (via @BotFather)\n- The message is a command (starts with /)\n- The bot is mentioned (@botname)\n\nSo I need to ask the user to check the bot's privacy settings or have them mention me in the group to see if that helps.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Message sent. But the real question is — can the bot *receive* messages from the group? In Telegram, by default bots only see:\n- Messages that **mention** them (@botname)\n- Commands (starting with /)\n- Replies to their own messages\n\nYou might need to **disable privacy mode** for the bot:\n\n1. Open **@BotFather** in Telegram\n2. Send `/mybots` → select your bot\n3. Go to **Bot Settings** → **Group Privacy** → turn it **OFF**\n\nThen remove and re-add the bot to the group.\n\nOr just try **mentioning me** in the group like `@NexaBot hi` — does that work?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":401,"output":600,"cacheRead":97984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98985,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774676358402}}
{"type":"message","id":"73a8919e","parentId":"4088aafe","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:49:13.472Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"122\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-28 05:49 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nOk so what if i am asking something here and same time people are talking to you in the group. How will you parallely handle that"}],"timestamp":1774676953460}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb1ab355","parentId":"73a8919e","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:50:08.157Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about concurrent handling of direct messages and group messages. Let me think about how this works technically in OpenClaw.\n\nIn OpenClaw, each chat (direct or group) creates its own session. So when someone messages in the group, it would create a separate session for that group chat, while the direct chat with Nemesis is a different session. These sessions run independently, so I can handle both simultaneously.\n\nLet me explain this clearly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"That's actually how it already works. Each chat gets its own session:\n\n- **This chat** (you + me) → one session\n- **Group chat** (Nrexya) → separate session\n\nThey run independently — like two separate conversations. When Sravya messages in the group, it triggers a new isolated turn for that session. Your direct chat isn't affected at all.\n\nThink of it like having two tabs open. I'm not \"splitting attention\" — each conversation is its own instance. The only shared resource is me, but sessions don't block each other.\n\nThe only thing to keep in mind: if both you and Sravya message at the exact same moment, there might be a tiny queue delay since the AI model processes requests sequentially. But in practice it's milliseconds — you'd never notice.\n\nSo yeah, go ahead and chat in the group while we talk here. It'll just work. ⚡"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":1148,"output":382,"cacheRead":97792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99322,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774676953470}}
