{"type":"message","id":"cccbee29","parentId":"af2e1b80","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:57:12.264Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the issue! The error is: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\"\n\nThe cron jobs are generating the messages successfully (the summaries look great!), but they can't deliver because they don't have a target chat ID configured. I need to update the cron jobs to specify the Telegram chat ID for delivery.\n\nLet me look at the cron job configuration. The jobs have `--announce --channel telegram` but they need a target. I should update the jobs to include the delivery target (Nemesis's chat ID: 7924461837).\n\nLet me edit the cron jobs to add the target.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it! The messages are being generated beautifully, but delivery fails with: `\"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\"`. The jobs don't know *where* to send the messages. Let me fix them."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b465c2839e2b4a479965802e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron edit --help 2>&1 | head -25"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":6983,"output":349,"cacheRead":101440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108772,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774677421392}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ecc6a2a","parentId":"cccbee29","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:57:15.018Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b465c2839e2b4a479965802e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Config warnings:\\n- plugins.entries.streamchat: plugin streamchat: plugin id mismatch (manifest uses \"streamchat\", entry hints \"openclaw-channel-streamchat\")\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — If something's on fire, I can't extinguish it—but I can write a beautiful postmortem.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron edit [options] <id>\n\nEdit a cron job (patch fields)\n\nArguments:\n  id                                   Job id\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>                       Channel account id for delivery\n                                       (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>                         Set agent id\n  --announce                           Announce summary to a chat\n                                       (subagent-style)\n  --at <when>                          Set one-shot time (ISO) or duration like\n                                       20m\n  --best-effort-deliver                Do not fail job if delivery fails\n  --channel <channel>                  Delivery channel (last)\n  --clear-agent                        Unset agent and use default (default:\n                                       false)\n  --clear-session-key                  Unset session key (default: false)\n  --cron <expr>                        Set cron expression"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2741,"aggregated":"Config warnings:\\n- plugins.entries.streamchat: plugin streamchat: plugin id mismatch (manifest uses \"streamchat\", entry hints \"openclaw-channel-streamchat\")\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — If something's on fire, I can't extinguish it—but I can write a beautiful postmortem.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron edit [options] <id>\n\nEdit a cron job (patch fields)\n\nArguments:\n  id                                   Job id\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>                       Channel account id for delivery\n                                       (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>                         Set agent id\n  --announce                           Announce summary to a chat\n                                       (subagent-style)\n  --at <when>                          Set one-shot time (ISO) or duration like\n                                       20m\n  --best-effort-deliver                Do not fail job if delivery fails\n  --channel <channel>                  Delivery channel (last)\n  --clear-agent                        Unset agent and use default (default:\n                                       false)\n  --clear-session-key                  Unset session key (default: false)\n  --cron <expr>                        Set cron expression","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774677435014}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed1a8ec9","parentId":"5ecc6a2a","timestamp":"2026-03-28T05:57:31.805Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the edit command options. The issue is that the delivery needs a target. Let me check if there's a `--to` or `--target` option for the edit command.\n\nActually, looking at the original cron add command, I used `--announce` and `--channel telegram`, but I never specified a target. The `--announce` option needs to know where to send the message. Let me check if there's a way to specify the target.\n\nLooking at the error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\", the job needs to know the chatId to deliver to. I need to either:\n1. Delete and recreate the jobs with the proper target\n\n\n2. Or find a way to edit the jobs to add the target\n\nLet me check the cron add help again to see if there's a `--to` flag.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d36c16ebf7b4414293fda53c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron edit --help 2>&1 | grep -i \"target\\|to\\|chat\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":7336,"output":397,"cacheRead":101568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109301,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774677435026}}
