{"type":"message","id":"2e5b7eac","parentId":"52237688","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:45:33.571Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_19b72c1ecf244a10bd97476f","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Dhurandhar 2 movie review 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"tookMs\": 6685,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"14a80e98546f182f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n\\\"Dhurandhar 2,\\\" officially titled \\\"Dhurandhar: The Revenge,\\\" was released worldwide on March 19, 2026, coinciding with Gudi Padwa, Ugadi, and Eid al-Fitr. The film, a sequel to the 2025 blockbuster \\\"Dhurandhar,\\\" stars Ranveer Singh, Arjun Rampal, Sanjay Dutt, and R. Madhavan, among others. It was also released in Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam, and Kannada languages, though the dubbed versions experienced a slight delay in some regions.\\n\\nReviews for \\\"Dhurandhar 2\\\" have been mixed. While some critics praise its ability to live up to the hype of the first part, highlighting entertaining twists, top-notch acting, and a tight script, others found it to be \\\"angrier, louder, and emptier\\\" than its predecessor.\\n\\nTimes Now lauded the film for its direction and writing, comparing Aditya Dhar's achievement to Anurag Kashyap's \\\"Gangs Of Wasseypur\\\" in creating two equally good films. The review particularly commended Ranveer Singh's performance, describing it as \\\"even more ghayal and ghatak\\\" (wounded and deadly). Karan Johar also praised the film, stating that Ranveer Singh delivered his \\\"career BEST work\\\" and calling Aditya Dhar an \\\"outstanding filmmaker\\\". He noted that the film's \\\"heart-wrenching backstory of Jaskirat\\\" and \\\"heartbreaking sacrifices\\\" resonated deeply.\\n\\nHowever, Newslaundry criticized \\\"Dhurandhar 2\\\" for its blatant pro-establishment propaganda and a lack of a strong antagonist, a role effectively filled by Akshaye Khanna in the first film. The review found the sequel to be hampered by its focus on propaganda over purpose, with Pakistani politics becoming a minor plot point and demonetisation taking center stage. The Indian Express also noted that while Ranveer Singh kept viewers engaged, the film \\\"lacks the 'mazaa' (fun) of the original\\\" despite its action, and missed Akshaye Khanna's character. Hindustan Times acknowledged Ranveer Singh's brilliant performance but felt the film's nuance and detailing weren't as sharp as the first part, and found the praise for the government \\\"heavy-handed\\\".\\n\\nThe film has achieved significant commercial success, crossing Rs 1,088 crore globally in its first week of release, making it one of the biggest blockbusters in Indian cinema history. Despite receiving an A (adults only) certificate for strong violence, it garnered praise for its cast's performances, storytelling, and musical score, while facing criticism for its levels of violence and alleged nationalist propaganda. It was banned in Gulf Cooperation Council countries, similar to its predecessor.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"14a80e98546f182f\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dhurandhar:_The_Revenge\",\n      \"title\": \"wikipedia.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/aditya-dhar-and-ranveer-singhs-dhurandhar-2-the-revenge-crosses-rs-1088-crore-at-global-box-office/article70795385.ece\",\n      \"title\": \"thehindu.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/dhurandhar-2-the-revenge-south-versions-release-date-why-was-the-ranveer-singh-starrer-delayed-in-tamil-telugu-and-malayalam/articleshow/129701213.cms\",\n      \"title\": \"indiatimes.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.newslaundry.com/2026/03/19/dhurandhar-the-revenge-review-hamzas-mission-is-bloodshed-dhars-mission-is-whitewash\",\n      \"title\": \"newslaundry.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment-news/reviews/dhurandhar-2-movie-review-ranveer-singh-starrer-imdb-review-ratings-public-reaction-review-153859757\",\n      \"title\": \"timesnownews.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/karan-johar-reviews-dhurandhar-2-the-revenge-ranveer-singh-delivers-his-career-best-calls-aditya-dhar-an-outstanding-filmmaker/articleshow/129852964.cms\",\n      \"title\": \"indiatimes.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/dhurandhar-2-movie-review-aditya-dhar-ranveer-singh-10589113/\",\n      \"title\": \"indianexpress.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/dhurandhar-2-review-rollercoaster-ride-elevated-by-ranveer-singh-brilliance-aditya-dhar-undoubtable-restraint-101773862482390.html\",\n      \"title\": \"hindustantimes.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Dhurandhar 2 movie review 2026","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","tookMs":6685,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"gemini","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"14a80e98546f182f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n\"Dhurandhar 2,\" officially titled \"Dhurandhar: The Revenge,\" was released worldwide on March 19, 2026, coinciding with Gudi Padwa, Ugadi, and Eid al-Fitr. The film, a sequel to the 2025 blockbuster \"Dhurandhar,\" stars Ranveer Singh, Arjun Rampal, Sanjay Dutt, and R. Madhavan, among others. It was also released in Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam, and Kannada languages, though the dubbed versions experienced a slight delay in some regions.\n\nReviews for \"Dhurandhar 2\" have been mixed. While some critics praise its ability to live up to the hype of the first part, highlighting entertaining twists, top-notch acting, and a tight script, others found it to be \"angrier, louder, and emptier\" than its predecessor.\n\nTimes Now lauded the film for its direction and writing, comparing Aditya Dhar's achievement to Anurag Kashyap's \"Gangs Of Wasseypur\" in creating two equally good films. The review particularly commended Ranveer Singh's performance, describing it as \"even more ghayal and ghatak\" (wounded and deadly). Karan Johar also praised the film, stating that Ranveer Singh delivered his \"career BEST work\" and calling Aditya Dhar an \"outstanding filmmaker\". He noted that the film's \"heart-wrenching backstory of Jaskirat\" and \"heartbreaking sacrifices\" resonated deeply.\n\nHowever, Newslaundry criticized \"Dhurandhar 2\" for its blatant pro-establishment propaganda and a lack of a strong antagonist, a role effectively filled by Akshaye Khanna in the first film. The review found the sequel to be hampered by its focus on propaganda over purpose, with Pakistani politics becoming a minor plot point and demonetisation taking center stage. The Indian Express also noted that while Ranveer Singh kept viewers engaged, the film \"lacks the 'mazaa' (fun) of the original\" despite its action, and missed Akshaye Khanna's character. Hindustan Times acknowledged Ranveer Singh's brilliant performance but felt the film's nuance and detailing weren't as sharp as the first part, and found the praise for the government \"heavy-handed\".\n\nThe film has achieved significant commercial success, crossing Rs 1,088 crore globally in its first week of release, making it one of the biggest blockbusters in Indian cinema history. Despite receiving an A (adults only) certificate for strong violence, it garnered praise for its cast's performances, storytelling, and musical score, while facing criticism for its levels of violence and alleged nationalist propaganda. It was banned in Gulf Cooperation Council countries, similar to its predecessor.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"14a80e98546f182f\">>>","citations":[{"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dhurandhar:_The_Revenge","title":"wikipedia.org"},{"url":"https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/aditya-dhar-and-ranveer-singhs-dhurandhar-2-the-revenge-crosses-rs-1088-crore-at-global-box-office/article70795385.ece","title":"thehindu.com"},{"url":"https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/dhurandhar-2-the-revenge-south-versions-release-date-why-was-the-ranveer-singh-starrer-delayed-in-tamil-telugu-and-malayalam/articleshow/129701213.cms","title":"indiatimes.com"},{"url":"https://www.newslaundry.com/2026/03/19/dhurandhar-the-revenge-review-hamzas-mission-is-bloodshed-dhars-mission-is-whitewash","title":"newslaundry.com"},{"url":"https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment-news/reviews/dhurandhar-2-movie-review-ranveer-singh-starrer-imdb-review-ratings-public-reaction-review-153859757","title":"timesnownews.com"},{"url":"https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/karan-johar-reviews-dhurandhar-2-the-revenge-ranveer-singh-delivers-his-career-best-calls-aditya-dhar-an-outstanding-filmmaker/articleshow/129852964.cms","title":"indiatimes.com"},{"url":"https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/dhurandhar-2-movie-review-aditya-dhar-ranveer-singh-10589113/","title":"indianexpress.com"},{"url":"https://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/dhurandhar-2-review-rollercoaster-ride-elevated-by-ranveer-singh-brilliance-aditya-dhar-undoubtable-restraint-101773862482390.html","title":"hindustantimes.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774709133567}}
{"type":"message","id":"67b5dc08","parentId":"2e5b7eac","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:46:02.688Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Web search works! Let me summarize the reviews for the user.Web search is working! Here's what the reviews say about Dhurandhar 2:\n\n**Dhurandhar: The Revenge** — released March 19, 2026. Ranveer Singh, Arjun Rampal, Sanjay Dutt, R. Madhavan. Directed by Aditya Dhar.\n\n**The good:**\n- Ranveer Singh is getting massive praise — Karan Johar called it his \"career BEST work\"\n- Times Now compared Aditya Dhar to Anurag Kashyap's Gangs of Wasseypur\n- Tight script, entertaining twists, top-notch acting\n- **₹1,088 crore globally in first week** — one of the biggest blockbusters in Indian cinema history\n\n**The bad:**\n- Some critics found it \"angrier, louder, and emptier\" than part 1\n- Misses Akshaye Khanna's character from the first film\n- Heavy-handed government praise / alleged propaganda\n- Not as much \"mazaa\" as the original\n\n**Verdict:** Massive commercial hit, mixed critical reception. Sounds like the action and Ranveer's performance carry it, but it's a bit more intense and less fun than the first one. Good pick though! 🔥\n\nNow I can actually search for stuff. The Gemini free tier should cover everything we need — AI daily digests, movie reviews, whatever. The setup's finally complete. ⚡","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":1520,"output":637,"cacheRead":121856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124013,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774709133579}}
