{"type":"message","id":"bfeabfcf","parentId":"7e064c26","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:25:31.526Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the issue. The log shows `\"reason\":\"no-mention\"` — the bot is receiving group messages but skipping them because nobody is mentioning the bot. This is Telegram's default privacy mode — the bot only sees messages that mention it or are commands.\n\nThe user needs to either:\n1. Disable privacy mode in @BotFather (Group Privacy → OFF)\n2. Or people need to @mention the bot in the group\n\nBut wait, the user said \"I didn't like the group convo\" — let me check if there are messages that the bot DID respond to, and what it said.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the issue. The log shows `\"reason\":\"no-mention\"` — the bot is receiving group messages but **only responding when someone mentions it** (@botname). That's Telegram's default privacy mode.\n\nThe messages you're seeing in the group are only triggered when someone explicitly tags me. Regular messages are being skipped.\n\n**Two options to fix this:**\n\n1. **Disable privacy mode** (so I see every message):\n   - Open **@BotFather** → `/mybots` → select your bot\n   - **Bot Settings** → **Group Privacy** → turn it **OFF**\n   - Remove and re-add the bot to the group\n\n2. **Keep it as is** — I only respond when mentioned, which is less annoying for Sravya\n\nWhich do you prefer? Also, what didn't you like about the convo — was it my responses, or just that I wasn't participating enough?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro:free","usage":{"input":6244,"output":433,"cacheRead":134976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141653,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774765513881}}
